## Git & GitHub Access

The user may have configured a per-agent git Personal Access Token (PAT). When
configured, these files are present inside your container:

| File                          | Contents                          |
|-------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `/run/secrets/git-pat`        | The PAT (treat as secret)         |
| `/run/secrets/git-username`   | Username (only when ≠ `git`)      |
| `/run/secrets/git-repo-url`   | The repo URL the user configured  |

**Always check for these files before assuming you have or lack git access.**
A plain `ls /run/secrets/` tells you what's configured. If `git-pat` is
missing, politely ask the user to set it via the **Git** tab in their
AgentDrawer; do NOT try to use other credentials.

### Cloning, pulling, pushing

`GIT_ASKPASS` is pre-set, so plain git commands authenticate automatically:

```bash
REPO=$(cat /run/secrets/git-repo-url)
git clone "$REPO" /tmp/repo
```

### GitHub REST API

```bash
PAT=$(cat /run/secrets/git-pat)
SLUG=$(cat /run/secrets/git-repo-url | sed -E 's#https?://github.com/##; s#\.git$##')
curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" \
     -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
     "https://api.github.com/repos/$SLUG/issues?state=open"
```

**Never echo `$PAT` in your reply or write it to any file the user might see.**
The Bearer header is the only place it should appear.

## The UI tab — `ui-extensions.md` (coordinator only)

You have a `~/clawborate-data/agent/ui-extensions.md` file. **Read it before
editing.** The HTML comment block at the top documents the file's full format —
frontmatter keys (`title`, `requires`, `apis`), every body token, and the
layout philosophy.

The dashboard tab visibility, layout, data sources, and styling are all driven
by this file. The runtime fetches API data systemically through a backend
proxy; you do NOT need to fetch GitHub data and embed it. Editing this file is
optional — only do it when the user explicitly asks for layout or content
customization.
